# üìö MongoDB Basic Commands

## 1Ô∏è‚É£ Show Databases

**Syntax:**

```js
show dbs
```

**Example:**

```js
show dbs
// Shows all available databases ‚Üí admin, config, local
```

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£ Use Database

**Syntax:**

```js
use <dbname>
```

**Example:**

```js
use studentDB
// Switches to studentDB (creates if not exists)
```

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£ Create Collection

**Syntax:**

```js
db.createCollection("<name>")
```

**Example:**

```js
db.createCollection("students")
// Creates a new collection named "students"
```

---

## 4Ô∏è‚É£ Drop Database

**Syntax:**

```js
db.dropDatabase()
```

**Example:**

```js
db.dropDatabase()
// Deletes the currently selected database
```

---

## 5Ô∏è‚É£ Show Collections

**Syntax:**

```js
show collections
```

**Example:**

```js
show collections
// Lists all collections in the current DB ‚Üí students, teachers
```

---

## 6Ô∏è‚É£ Drop Collection

**Syntax:**

```js
db.<collection>.drop()
```

**Example:**

```js
db.students.drop()
// Deletes the "students" collection
```

---

## 7Ô∏è‚É£ Insert One Document

**Syntax:**

```js
db.<collection>.insertOne({ key: value })
```

**Example:**

```js
db.students.insertOne({ name: "Rahul", age: 22 })
// Inserts one student record into "students" collection
```

---

## 8Ô∏è‚É£ Insert Many Documents

**Syntax:**

```js
db.<collection>.insertMany([{...}, {...}])
```

**Example:**

```js
db.students.insertMany([
  { name: "Shreyas", age: 21 },
  { name: "Amit", age: 21 }
])
// Inserts multiple student records in one go
```

---

## 9Ô∏è‚É£ Find Documents

**Syntax:**

```js
db.<collection>.find()
```

**Example:**

```js
db.students.find()
// Retrieves all documents inside "students"
```

---
